<concept id="concept_E8D43EB4494E41D2AB42D4A89396D1AB"
                    xml:lang="en-us">
    <title>Prerequisites and Preparations</title>
    <conbody>
        <section>
            <p>As a prerequisite for using the HTTPS protocol, it is required to create a keystore.</p>
            <p>To create a keystore, log in to the host where the <ph
                    conref="../../shared/product-name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"/> Service is installed. </p>
            <p>Example for creating a keystore with the Keytool utility:</p>
            <codeblock>mkdir /opt/keystore
cd /opt/keystore
keytool -genkeypair -keystore monasca.keystore -alias testmonasca</codeblock>
        </section>
    </conbody>
</concept>
